<body>
    <h1>T10 - Technical Document</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"f5aad6b0fd22" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-1.Introdu=
ction">1. Introduction</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"0c49a609d1d4" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-1.1Purpose">1.1 P=
urpose</h2>
<p local-id=3D"e090c10194a4">This document describes the implementation of =
a centralized infrastructure monitoring solution using <strong>Amazon Cloud=
Watch</strong> to monitor multiple <strong>Amazon EC2</strong> instances.</=
p>
<p local-id=3D"6c1b65dd23b2">The goal is to provide a <strong>compact monit=
oring dashboard</strong> that allows teams to quickly understand infrastruc=
ture health.</p>
<p local-id=3D"541a7ac7fd73">The dashboard was designed using the <strong>5=
-second rule</strong>, meaning anyone viewing it should understand system h=
ealth within a few seconds.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a84c5f8b02af"><strong>Target audience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bfbbdc9e9920">CTO</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f82e201ed614">DevOps Engineers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"855a6ec546e3">Developers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"750456d56611">Solution Architects</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8a7cd59cd46b">Infrastructure Teams</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5319cf7630f6">Resellers</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"97273b01db44" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-1.2Scope">1.2 Sco=
pe</h2>
<p local-id=3D"e1a8e0ac142f">This project covers the implementation of infr=
astructure monitoring including:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"45a0ed3262a2">Launching EC2 instances</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b5a6500f5bf0">Enabling detailed monitoring</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8a89cbc372ab">Installing CloudWatch Agent</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"78a1ffdc1cba">Collecting infrastructure metrics</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"edd851728fd2">Designing a centralized monitoring dashboard</=
p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"153c06424679">Metrics monitored:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1f22d3a696c3">CPU Utilization</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f685f3e2b96b">Memory Usage</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"faffacc8112d">Disk Usage</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cae850e920c5">Network In</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0a870d06e865">Network Out</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ea17e9be0058">The solution focuses on <strong>infrastructure=
 observability using AWS monitoring services</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"28364c7da231" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-2.OverviewofDevOp=
sProject">2. Overview of DevOps Project</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"11bb4d5fd2f5" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-2.1Definition">2.=
1 Definition</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9eed61b67e75">DevOps monitoring provides continuous visibili=
ty into infrastructure and application performance. It helps operations tea=
ms detect issues early, optimize resources, and maintain system reliability=
.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f897375c541b">This project implements monitoring using <stro=
ng>Amazon CloudWatch</strong> to provide centralized observability of EC2 i=
nstances.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"5d4e80f9d5ca" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-2.2KeyPrinciples(=
AWSWell-ArchitectedFramework)">2.2 Key Principles (AWS Well-Architected Fra=
mework)</h2>
<p local-id=3D"c4671b1465b7">The solution aligns with the <strong>six pilla=
rs of the AWS Well-Architected Framework</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b1661ca9321e"><strong>Operational Excellence</strong><br>
Centralized monitoring enables faster issue detection and operational effic=
iency.</p>
<p local-id=3D"8948f9bb087e"><strong>Security</strong><br>
IAM roles and secure access policies control monitoring permissions.</p>
<p local-id=3D"13cfe994d8d3"><strong>Reliability</strong><br>
Monitoring helps detect abnormal system behavior before failures occur.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1c937c7b8e46"><strong>Performance Efficiency</strong><br>
Real-time metrics help identify CPU, memory, or network bottlenecks.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ae709212a412"><strong>Cost Optimization</strong><br>
Lightweight EC2 instances and efficient monitoring reduce operational costs=
.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7a6e8857a0f8"><strong>Sustainability</strong><br>
Monitoring enables better resource utilization and avoids unnecessary infra=
structure usage.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"bcb9c34e7907" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-2.3GoalsandObject=
ives">2.3 Goals and Objectives</h2>
<p local-id=3D"fcd542593642">The key objectives of this project include:</p=
>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7c38d61369d0">Create a centralized monitoring dashboard</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2f325f886b87">Monitor multiple EC2 instances simultaneously<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f3b100647a57">Provide clear infrastructure visibility</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"af84476290ab">Detect abnormal performance behavior</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ac4180aedec4">Design an easily understandable dashboard</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"bc2250dcfc31" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-2.4Constraintsand=
Assumptions">2.4 Constraints and Assumptions</h2>
<p local-id=3D"719ba11ba406"><strong>Constraints</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8d1fc1b2ce96">Project completion time: <strong>3 hours</stro=
ng></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8e99bdb183d6">Limited infrastructure setup</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cc93572b930b">Monitoring limited to EC2 instances</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3cae2acba85f"><strong>Assumptions</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cea6c34fd0d9">All EC2 instances operate within the same AWS =
account</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a4a2054ae7d5">CloudWatch Agent is installed on each instance=
</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0d56a03d5d16">Metrics are available through CloudWatch</p></=
li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"4801a5b43003" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-3.Architectureand=
Infrastructure">3. Architecture and Infrastructure</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"4c3292af3d43" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-3.1Infrastructure=
Overview">3.1 Infrastructure Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"99e4a1b25b65">The infrastructure consists of <strong>four EC=
2 instances</strong> representing application and testing workloads.</p>
<p local-id=3D"40fc56e9661a">Each instance sends system metrics to CloudWat=
ch, where the metrics are visualized through a centralized monitoring dashb=
oard.</p>
<p local-id=3D"76c1bd343b72">Architecture flow:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">EC2 Ins=
tances
      =E2=86=93
CloudWatch Agent
      =E2=86=93
CloudWatch Metrics
      =E2=86=93
CloudWatch Dashboard</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"f9ebc9eb2431" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-3.2Environments">=
3.2 Environments</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ef30e2ad0eb5">The solution simulates a <strong>production mo=
nitoring environment</strong> where multiple EC2 instances represent applic=
ation servers.</p>
<p local-id=3D"bdb55d0047b7">The monitoring dashboard provides a unified vi=
ew of system performance across all servers.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"20f8a1d390e9" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-3.4ApplicationArc=
hitecture&amp;UserRequestFlow">3.4 Application Architecture &amp; User Requ=
est Flow</h2>
<p local-id=3D"82346b2430c3">User requests are handled by EC2 instances.</p=
>
<p local-id=3D"ca05f50438d9">System metrics are collected through the Cloud=
Watch Agent and transmitted to CloudWatch where they are visualized using d=
ashboard widgets.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"86f3ab1fa1ba" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-3.3ToolsandTechno=
logies">3.3 Tools and Technologies</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"2=
cc5b8d4-07f5-4a5b-a599-d6eeeb6ad9f4" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"88d8dbeb798a">Tool</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"3e060cdaedff">Purpose</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1d4b1e86d180">Amazon EC2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a3b61fdc99c6">Compute infrastructure</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"36f4f8eb03e2">Amazon CloudWatch</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0d561bc05a57">Monitoring and observability</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f7ce0b8a34c8">CloudWatch Agent</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b16325feb5bf">Collect system-level metrics</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a403f56dd1ee">Linux (Amazon Linux 2023)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ec0763e5a838">Operating system</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"42318c184e9b">IAM</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5cf29a1c1557">Access management</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"7e48f3fdc5b4" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-4.DevelopmentPrac=
tices">4. Development Practices</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"8fcba422de7d" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-4.1VersionControl=
">4.1 Version Control</h2>
<p local-id=3D"1864db29df96">Infrastructure configuration follows standard =
DevOps practices for maintainability and reproducibility.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"eb400c9e51a6" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-4.2ContinuousInte=
gration">4.2 Continuous Integration</h2>
<p local-id=3D"c6e0106fa5b2">CI pipelines were not implemented in this moni=
toring-focused setup but can be integrated in future enhancements.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"a96078481a9f" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-4.3AutomatedTesti=
ng">4.3 Automated Testing</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a6e7a2c31f01">Automated testing was not required for this in=
frastructure monitoring implementation.</p>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"679d969e942f" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-4.4CodeQualityand=
Analysis">4.4 Code Quality and Analysis</h2>
<p local-id=3D"c1a699769620">Configuration files and scripts follow standar=
d DevOps configuration practices.</p>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"04dcdd1ecd7c" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-5.DeploymentandRe=
leaseManagement">5. Deployment and Release Management</h1>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"272236e9fe74" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-Step1=E2=80=93Lau=
nchEC2Instances">Step 1 =E2=80=93 Launch EC2 Instances</h1>
<p local-id=3D"84f8208ddb2b">Four EC2 instances were launched to simulate a=
pplication infrastructure.</p>
<p local-id=3D"cd87ffa60b43">Example instance names:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1dc0dac0d1f6">test-server-1</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4dbb44722b58">test-server-2</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f623482868fa">test-server-3</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f4e8cf67d833">test-server-4</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"cc26eab4228b">These instances generate the infrastructure me=
trics used for monitoring.</p>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"5c7bd4651a0a" id=3D"T10-TechnicalDocument-Step2=E2=80=93Ena=
bleDetailedMonitoring">Step 2 =E2=80=93 Enable Detailed Monitoring</h1>
<p local-id=3D"40354c2ded3b">Detailed monitoring was enabled for each EC2 i=
nstance.</p>
<p local-id=3D"570c1ba14604">By default, EC2 sends metrics to CloudWatch ev=
ery <strong>5 minutes</strong>. Enabling detailed monitoring improves this =
to <strong>1-minute intervals</strong>, providing more accurate monitoring =
data.</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapp=
er confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image=
 image-center" alt=3D"Screenshot 2026-03-06 133442-20260306-080442.png" wid=
th=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"53f9c8662ff4f8296dbe3bceb669c60ee2a8369f=
91de3c5e291faf9a7f7c3e8b" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wi=
ki/download/attachments/1837039669/Screenshot%202026-03-06%20133442-2026030=
6-080442.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1772868253721&amp;cacheVers=
